<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-18T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-18T03:00:00-05:00" n="344" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.74/14: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Earle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-18T10:00:00+02:00">July 18,
                                    1941—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 3:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>317. The entire Bulgarian press controlled and censored by the Government
                            is rabidly pro-German. In spite of increasingly bitter articles against
                            our country there is as yet no visible evidence of ill will toward
                            America on the part of the people. There remains still a strong memory
                            of all the good deeds of America and Americans for Bulgaria.</p>
                        <p>However, with a steady increase in the number and intensity of these
                            press attacks on us an effect on the people must ultimately occur.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Earle</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>